+---
+name: qyl-frontend-contract
+description: Use this skill when building qyl frontend code, Base UI components, shadcn-based product UI, telemetry dashboards, logs/traces/spans explorers, MCP-facing workflows, loom investigation UI, TanStack Table data surfaces, or observability charts with ECharts. Enforces qyl's strict Base UI contract and prevents Radix pattern leakage.
+---
+
+# qyl-frontend-contract
+
+## When to use
+
+Use this skill whenever you are working on:
+
+- qyl frontend code
+- reusable product UI
+- design-system code
+- telemetry dashboards and explorer surfaces
+- logs, traces, spans, incidents, and alerts UI
+- MCP-facing product surfaces
+- loom investigation and root-cause workflows
+
+## Core contract
+
+qyl frontend uses:
+
+- shadcn as the source-owned shell and block layer
+- Base UI as the only primitive family
+- Tailwind + CSS variables as the styling baseline
+- TanStack Table + TanStack Virtual for large tabular surfaces
+- ECharts for dense observability charts
+- Recharts only for lightweight dashboard visuals
+- React Bits only for non-critical polish
+
+Base UI rules:
+
+- use only `@base-ui/react`
+- never import `@radix-ui/*` or `radix-ui`
+- never use `asChild`
+- never use `Slot`
+- compose through Base UI `render`
+- use `createHandle()` for detached triggers
+
+## Load the relevant rule file
+
+For implementation details, load the matching file:
+
+- `./rules/base-ui-composition.md`
+- `./rules/shadcn-foundation.md`
+- `./rules/styling-and-theming.md`
+- `./rules/tables-and-virtualization.md`
+- `./rules/charts.md`
+- `./rules/mcp-and-loom-surfaces.md`
+- `./rules/motion-and-polish.md`
+- `./rules/performance-and-density.md`
+- `./rules/ci-and-enforcement.md`
+- `./rules/done-and-fail-criteria.md`
